column33: Late got lost! Tag: RG on lek.

column13: About 6 inches snow fell night before last

column20: 2 birds of unknown sex flew from down S of lek
column33: At 7:17, R/R showed up - (?) S of lek - never strutted. 5:59 - 3 males arrived from draw (1 juv, 2 adults). R/B -  tail wagging + clucking w/UM male. 6:07 - 5 males arrived from draw. A lot of chasing of juv males. 6:23 - all birds but 1 down for ~ 30 sec. 6:27 - 2 hens around - everyone went crazy - chasing each other + strutting. R/B + UM male w/ copulation  and a standoff. UM male -  that had copulated attempted third copulation w/ hen, interrupted by neighboring male. Hen wandered off. Hen came back a few minutes later and solicited from same UM male. He didn't respond, she wandered off, then came back. She's desperate! See (?) and for about 1/2 min hen w/ same M male. She solicited again - he mated. Finaly! Copulation w/ same male interupted - whole process - 45min.

6:46 - Copulation attempted but interrupted by /R (x2). R/R (referring to copulation) I think but not sure on left tag. Cop at 5:42 may have been R/R or R/G - light was inadequate. I thought right was red but R/G was in some position (after therefore I may have not seen enough color but he was clearly a marked male). R/B - #961 Blue tag. R/G - #1040 Green tag. R/R. 6:05 - R/B in standoff with unmarked male. 6:07 -- won over another --. Birds flushed at 6:48. 6:30 R/R off by himself to SE of lek

column13: Snow overnight (1/2") at 6:00 - wind picked up to ~10mph w/ gusts.
column33: (Referring to cop.): w/ B/Y. Marked males: R/B R/G R/R. R/R got chased by everyone (juv). 7:09 - about 1/2 hens flew away, R/B chased off R/R(juv) severval times. B/Y solicited from R/B, bot no response

column20: Still quite dark, lots of strutting
column33: Too dark to tell who bred - R/B in group of 3 possible males. R/B was mad, tried to knock male off but was too late, hen solicited UM male not R/B, R/B was not strutting at time of solicitation or copulation.

Male: R/B. Most males flew at 5:47 -- to SE. Acted as though spooked by predator but we couldn't see anything.
I got out of truck at 6:05.. coyote making terrific racket off to NW -- could be coyotes spooked birds
6:31 - hens flew away - S. all strutting stopped. R/B standoff w/UM male - clucking + tail wagging but mostly sitting. Hen hanging out w/ 3 UM male. Golden eagle nest blew down.
Copulation - w/ male ?/G. Female ?/B, Male ?/B, Male ?/G. 5:36 - hawk flew by + all flew away. Hawk unsuccessful. Perched on S ridge from lek (1/4 mile away). 6:10 hawk gone

5:47 - all but 5 males flew E - were some northern harriers just below ridge when drove in. Remaining 5 strutted a lot! R/B.  5:57 - 3 more males flew E. Birds that flew only about 100 m to E, but no strutting. Golden eagle on ridge ~1/2 mile away.
At ~ 5:40 most males (8) flew  - may be due to movement of trucks as all were trying to get close enought to see net. Cannon net not fired

column20: Some males strutting (mostly juven), many marked

column13: Snow overnight + high winds - cannon net
column33: Lots of activity - 2? female solicited several males (including R/B) + no response because males kept fighting + chasing each other off. 5:46 - wind has really picked up. R/B - interrupted copulation!! Female solicited again - UM male twice - interrupted by 3 other males - including R/B

column20: R/B fighting later after males - R/R present
No strutting, 3 juv, small squabbles between adults + juvenile
column33: As female draw in ~ 15 birds flew to W. Hens flew at 5:28. 1 adult male terrorize 2 juveniles + 1 ? adult so bad they flew away. No marked birds. 6:37 all birds flew.

column28: Who cares ?? No hens around ?? No strutting
column33: 5:29 - 1 hen flew E - cannot find 2nd one. Y/O tail wagging + clucking w/UM male - wing beating + grabbing by neck - standoff. Nobody strutting after hen left. R/B chased off by UM male.
